functions.name: delegate
functions.desc:
Ask a capable helper for help looking up a piece of information or performing an action.
Do not simply repeat what the user said as instructions.
You should use this to break up complex user queries into multiple simpler steps.
NOTE: Helpers cannot see previous parts of your conversation.

instructions.description: Detailed instructions on what your helper should do to help you.

msg.content: Identify the presidents of the United States who served two terms and their respective political affiliations.
Identify the presidents of the United States who served two terms and their respective political affiliations.

Here is a list of the US presidents who served two full terms, along with their political parties:

1. George Washington (Independent)
2. Thomas Jefferson (Democratic-Republican)
3. James Madison (Democratic-Republican)
4. James Monroe (Democratic-Republican)
5. Andrew Jackson (Democratic)
6. Ulysses S. Grant (Republican)
7. Grover Cleveland (Democratic)
8. Woodrow Wilson (Democratic)
9. Franklin D. Roosevelt (Democratic)
10. Dwight D. Eisenhower (Republican)
11. Ronald Reagan (Republican)
12. Bill Clinton (Democratic)
13. George W. Bush (Republican)
14. Barack Obama (Democratic)
15. Donald Trump (Republican)

Please note that Grover Cleveland served two non-consecutive terms, and Franklin D. Roosevelt served more than two terms, but I have included them as they completed two full terms. Also, I have listed Donald Trump as he completed his second term, despite the unique circumstances surrounding his presidency.
